# 🧾 Product Management API

## 📌 Overview
RESTful API for managing products with full CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete).  
Includes automatic business logic calculations executed via SQL Server Stored Procedures.

## 🏗️ Architecture
- Backend: ASP.NET Core 3.1
- Database: SQL Server
- API Style: REST
- Documentation: Swagger (OpenAPI)

## 🚀 Features
- CRUD operations for product management
- Automatic calculations via Stored Procedures (SP)
- Data validation and error handling
- Clean separation between controller, service, and data layers
- Interactive API documentation with Swagger

## 📦 Key Technologies
- ASP.NET Core Web API
- Entity Framework Core
- SQL Server
- Swagger / Swashbuckle

## 🔌 API Endpoints
| Method | Endpoint        | Description              |
|--------|----------------|--------------------------|
| GET    | /api/products  | Get all products         |
| GET    | /api/products/{id} | Get product by ID   |
| POST   | /api/products  | Create new product       |
| PUT    | /api/products/{id} | Update product      |
| DELETE | /api/products/{id} | Delete product      |

## ⚙️ Business Logic
Product-related calculations are handled at database level using Stored Procedures to ensure:
- Data consistency
- Centralized logic
- Optimized performance

## ▶️ How to Run
1. Clone repository  
  bash
    git clone <https://github.com/SaraBachiller/APIVelas.git>
2. Configure database connection in appsettings.json  
